claim.claim-text:
1. A flat panel television console and support kit for use in a plurality of different configurations comprising:
a flat panel television console having a front side and a back side, and an upper shelf,
said flat panel television console being capable of use in a standalone configuration to support a flat panel television on an upper surface of said upper shelf;

a spine which becomes an integral component of said console when a lower end of said spine is optionally secured to said back side of said console,
said spine extending from said back side of said console to above said upper surface of said upper shelf and terminating in an upper end positioned above said upper shelf when said spine is secured to said console; and

a flat panel television mounting assembly secured to said upper end of said spine providing an elevated support for supporting a flat panel television above said upper surface of said upper shelf of said console;
said kit being used in a first configuration wherein a flat panel television is supported on said upper surface of said upper shelf of said console;
said kit being used in a second configuration wherein a flat panel television is secured to said flat panel television mounting assembly and said flat panel television mounting assembly is secured to a wall,
said kit being used in a third configuration wherein a flat panel television is secured to said flat panel television mounting assembly, and said flat panel television mounting assembly is secured at said upper end of said spine, and said spine is secured to said console to support said flat panel television above said console.

6. A flat panel television console and support kit for use in a plurality of different configurations comprising:
a flat panel television console having a front side and a back side and an upper shelf, said flat panel television console being capable of use in a standalone configuration to support a flat panel television on an upper surface of said upper shelf;
an elongated spine which becomes an integral component of said console when a lower end of said spine is optionally secured to said back side of said console,
said spine extending from said back side of said console to above said upper surface of said upper shelf and terminating in an upper end positioned above said upper shelf when said spine is secured to said console;
a flat panel television mounting assembly secured to said upper end of said spine providing an elevated support for supporting a flat panel television above said upper surface of said upper shelf of said console;
a flat panel television mounting frame; and
a pair of panel brackets,
said kit being used in a first configuration wherein a flat panel television is supported on said upper surface of said upper shelf of said console,
said kit being used in a second configuration wherein said console is used in a standalone configuration and said flat panel television is mounted to a wall whereby said panel brackets are secured to a back surface of said flat panel television, said panel brackets are further secured to said flat panel television mounting frame and said flat panel television mounting frame is secured to said wall,
said kit being used in a third configuration wherein said panel brackets are secured to a back surface of said flat panel television, said panel brackets are further secured to said flat panel television mounting frame and said flat panel television mounting frame is secured to said flat panel television mounting assembly at said upper end of said spine, and said spine is secured to said back side of said console whereby said flat panel television is supported above said upper surface of said upper shelf of console.

10. A flat panel television console and support kit for use in a plurality of different configurations comprising:
a flat panel television console having a front side and a back side and an upper shelf;
a first short spine which forms a structural supporting component of said console;
a second long spine, having a height which extends above said upper surface of said upper shelf terminating in an upper end which provides an elevated support for a flat panel television, said second long spine forming a structural supporting component of said console; and
a flat panel television mounting structure;
said kit being used in a first configuration wherein said first short spine is secured to said console, and a flat panel television is supported on said upper surface of said upper shelf of said console,
said kit being used in a second configuration wherein a flat panel television is secured to said flat panel television mounting structure and said flat panel television mounting structure is secured to a wall,
said kit being used in a third configuration wherein a flat panel television is secured to said flat panel television mounting structure, and said flat panel television mounting structure is secured to said upper end of said second long spine, and said second long spine is secured to said back side of said console to support said flat panel television above said console.

15. A flat panel television console and support kit for use in a plurality of different configurations comprising:
a flat panel television console having a front side and a back side and an upper shelf;
a first short spine which forms a structural supporting component of said console;
a second long spine, having a height which extends above said upper surface of said upper shelf terminating in an upper end which provides an elevated support for a flat panel television, said second long spine forming a structural supporting component of said console;
a pair of panel brackets; and
a flat panel television mounting structure;
said kit being used in a first configuration wherein said first short spine is secured to said console, and a flat panel television is supported on said upper surface of said upper shelf of said console,
said kit being used in a second configuration wherein said panel brackets are secured to a back side of said flat panel television, said panel brackets are secured to said flat panel television mounting structure and said flat panel television mounting structure is secured to a wall,
said kit being used in a third configuration wherein said panel brackets are secured to a back side of a flat panel television, said panel brackets are secured to said flat panel television mounting structure, said flat panel television mounting structure is secured to said upper end of said second long spine, and said second long spine is secured to said back side of said console to support said flat panel television above said console.
